# **38. Ports**

## Definition

A Port is a logical number that identifies a particular application or service running on a device.

While an IP address identifies the device, a Port identifies the application.

---

## Real-Life Analogy

|Real Life|Networking|
|---|---|
|Building Address|IP Address|
|Apartment Number|Port Number|

---

## Example

```
Laptop

192.168.1.20

↓

Chrome

Port 52134

↓

Google

Port 443
```

---

